SUMMARY:Debate Board: GenAI and Language Learning
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an interactive Debate Board where students\, facu
 lty\, and staff are invited to share their perspectives on the role of ge
 nerative AI in language learning. This informal\, drop-in activity encour
 ages critical thinking and open dialogue about how emerging technologies 
 are shaping our academic and professional lives.  Participants will be pr
 ompted to respond to two guiding questions:How do you feel about using Ge
 nAI for language learning?How does GenAI work for you in your language le
 arning?  Using post-it notes\, you will be able to contribute brief writt
 en responses to these questions. You'll also have the opportunity to read
  and reflect on others' viewpoints\, creating a collective snapshot of ou
 r community's perspectives. Stop by\, share your thoughts\, and join the 
 conversation!Time: April 9 (Thursday) 10 AM-3 pm. This activity will take
  place concurrently with the event "America's Role in the World."Location
 : Find us in the hallway near Shreve Auditorium (GA 0001)\, next to the c
 offee table setup for the America's Role Conference. We will have some sw
 eet treats\, too.Organizer: Center for Language Technology
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p data-start="44" data-end="104">  Join us 
 for an interactive Debate Board where students\, faculty\, and staff are 
 invited to share their perspectives on the role of generative AI in langu
 age learning. This informal\, drop-in activity encourages critical thinki
 ng and open dialogue about how emerging technologies are shaping our acad
 emic and professional lives.</p><p data-start="44" data-end="104">  Parti
 cipants will be prompted to respond to two guiding questions:</p><ul><li 
 data-start="44" data-end="104"><strong>How do you feel about using GenAI 
 for language learning?</strong></li><li data-start="44" data-end="104"><s
 trong>How does GenAI work for you in your language learning?</strong></li
 ></ul><p>  Using post-it notes\, you will be able to contribute brief wri
 tten responses to these questions. You'll also have the opportunity to re
 ad and reflect on others' viewpoints\, creating a collective snapshot of 
 our community's perspectives. Stop by\, share your thoughts\, and join th
 e conversation!</p><p><strong>Time:</strong> April 9 (Thursday) 10 AM-3 p
 m. This activity will take place concurrently with the event "<em>America
 's Role in the World</em>."</p><p><strong>Location:</strong> Find us in t
 he hallway near <strong>Shreve Auditorium (GA 0001)</strong>\, next to th
 e coffee table setup for the America's Role Conference. We will have some
  sweet treats\, too.</p><p><strong>Organizer:</strong> Center for Languag
 e Technology</p>
