 Ķ–Ľ–Ķ–ľ\, —Ā–Ņ–Ķ—Ü–ł–į–Ľ–ł–∑–ł—Ä—É—é—Č–ł–ľ—Ā—Ź –Ĺ–į –≥—Ä–į–∂–ī–į–Ĺ—Ā–ļ–ĺ–
 ľ –ĺ–Ī—Č–Ķ—Ā—ā–≤–Ķ\, –Ņ–ĺ–Ľ–ł—ā–ł—á–Ķ—Ā–ļ–ĺ–Ļ —ā—Ä–į–Ĺ—Ā—Ą–ĺ—Ä–ľ–į—Ü–ł–ł 
 –ł –Ĺ–į—Ü–ł–ĺ–Ĺ–į–Ľ—Ć–Ĺ–ĺ–Ļ –ł–ī–Ķ–Ĺ—ā–ł—á–Ĺ–ĺ—Ā—ā–ł.Ilya Silich is a Bel
 arusian activist-in-exile\, IT specialist\, and former elected representa
 tive in the digital grassroots democracy initiative "–°—Ö–ĺ–ī" (Assembly)
  in Brest. He supervised volunteers and monitored elections in 2020 as a 
 member of civic engagement initiative "–ß–Ķ—Ā—ā–Ĺ—č–Ķ –õ—é–ī–ł" (Honest P
 eople). Ilya hold degrees in art studies from the Belarusian State Academ
 y of Arts. He is currently an independent researcher with a focus on civi
 l society\, political transformation\, and national identity.
