SUMMARY:"Global\, Sustainable\, Digital: How Entrepreneurs Change the Wor
 ld?" with Magdalena Marczewska
DESCRIPTION:This seminar explores how startups expand globally in a digit
 al and sustainability-focused world. Many new companies reach internation
 al customers from day one using online platforms and digital tools. The t
 alk explains how entrepreneurs combine technology\, global opportunities\
 , and responsible business practices to grow their ventures and compete i
 n today's rapidly changing economy.Magdalena Marczewska is a Senior Resea
 rch Fellow and KoŇõciuszko Foundation Fellow at Indiana University and a 
 faculty member at the University of Warsaw. Her research focuses on innov
 ation\, technology management\, and digital transformation. Combining aca
 demic and industry experience\, she works as an Innovation Coach supporti
 ng startups and leads international research projects on entrepreneurship
 \, sustainable business\, and strategy.Sponsored by the Polish Studies Ce
 nter
