SUMMARY:Spring 2026 Colloquium Series with Eduardo Herrera
DESCRIPTION:The Center for Latin American and Caribbean Studies is proud 
 to present the continuation of its Colloquium Series for Spring 2026.  We
  welcome Dr. Eduardo Herrera&#160\;as he presents Argentina's Soccer Chan
 ting Tradition\, from Neighborhood Stadiums to Global Stages.  &#160\;Edu
 ardo Herrera is an associate professor in the department of Folklore and 
 Ethnomusicology and the director of the Ethnomusicology Institute at Indi
 ana University Bloomington. With a PhD from University of Illinois Urbana
 -Champaign\, His research comprises topics from sound studies to Latinx c
 ultural practices and coloniality/postcoloniality/decoloniality.  The CLA
 CS Spring 2026 Colloquium meets Mondays from February through April\, wit
 h faculty and guest speakers engaging Latin America and the Caribbean thr
 ough research on history\, culture\, language\, politics\, and the arts. 
 Check the CLACS Calendar (https://events.iu.edu/clacs/) for details.
